  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How much cubic meter of cement, sand required for 12mm cement sand plaster 1:6 for 950 sq m?",
  "response": "To calculate the amount of cement and sand required for 12mm plaster with a ratio of 1:6 over an area of 950 square meters, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Determine the volume of plaster**:\n   - Thickness of plaster = 12 mm = 0.012 meters\n   - Area to be plastered = 950 sqm\n   - Volume of plaster = Area \u00d7 Thickness = 950 sqm \u00d7 0.012 m = 11.4 cubic meters\n\n2. **Calculate the amount of ingredients based on the mix ratio**:\n   - The mix ratio is 1:6, meaning 1 part cement and 6 parts sand.\n   - Total parts = 1 (cement) + 6 (sand) = 7 parts\n\n3. **Calculate the cement and sand requirement**:\n   - **Cement volume** = (1/7) \u00d7 Total Volume of Plaster = (1/7) \u00d7 11.4 = 1.6286 cubic meters\n   - **Sand volume** = (6/7) \u00d7 Total Volume of Plaster = (6/7) \u00d7 11.4 = 9.7714 cubic meters\n\n4. **Convert cement volume to bags**:\n   - The density of cement = 1440 kg/m\u00b3\n   - 1 bag of cement = 50 kg\n   - Volume of one bag of cement = 50 kg / 1440 kg/m\u00b3 = 0.0347 m\u00b3\n   - Number of cement bags required = Cement volume / Volume of one bag = 1.6286 m\u00b3 / 0.0347 m\u00b3/bag \u2248 47 bags\n\nTherefore, for 950 sq meters of 12mm thick plaster, you would need approximately 47 bags of cement and 9.77 cubic meters of sand. Note that these calculations do not take into account waste or additional materials that may be needed for other reasons. Adjust quantities as necessary for practical use and conditions.",
